# JumpServer API Conventions

## Authentication
- Uses HMAC-SHA256 request signing (PAM Application keys)
- KEY_ID and KEY_SECRET from PAM > Application Management
- Every request must include signed headers: `(request-target)`, `accept`, `date`, `x-jms-org`

## API Endpoints
- Users: `GET /api/v1/users/users/`
- Assets: `GET /api/v2/assets/assets/`
- Permissions: `/api/v1/perms/asset-permissions/` (GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE)
- Sessions: `GET /api/v2/terminal/sessions/`
- Account Secret: `GET /api/v1/accounts/integration-applications/account-secret/`

## Response Handling
- Paginated endpoints return `{"results": [...]}` — always check for this
- Use `data.get("results", data) if isinstance(data, dict) else data`

## JIT Permission Naming
- Prefix all JIT permissions with `jit-` for easy identification and cleanup
- Format: `jit-{username}-{hostname}-{YYYYMMDDHHmmSS}`

## Client Pattern
- All methods are `async def` but use synchronous `requests` internally
- Always call `await client.close()` in a `finally` block
